  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is your most effective link building strategy in 2016?",
  "response": "In 2016, effective link building strategies focused on quality over quantity and emphasized creating valuable content that naturally attracted backlinks. Here are some key strategies that were effective during that time:\n\n1. **Content Marketing**: Creating high-quality, informative, and engaging content that addresses the needs and interests of your target audience. This could include blog posts, infographics, videos, and research studies that others would want to link to.\n\n2. **Guest Blogging**: Writing guest posts for reputable websites within your niche. This not only helped build backlinks but also allowed you to reach new audiences and establish authority.\n\n3. **Broken Link Building**: Finding broken links on other websites and reaching out to the webmasters to suggest replacing the broken link with your own relevant content. This approach provided value to the webmaster while earning you a backlink.\n\n4. **Resource Pages**: Identifying resource pages in your industry that curate valuable links and reaching out to suggest your content as a useful addition.\n\n5. **Skyscraper Technique**: Finding popular content in your niche, creating something even better, and then reaching out to those who linked to the original content to inform them about your improved version.\n\n6. **Influencer Outreach**: Building relationships with influencers in your industry and encouraging them to share your content. This could lead to valuable backlinks and increased visibility.\n\n7. **Social Media Promotion**: Sharing your content on social media platforms to increase its reach and the likelihood of earning backlinks from others who find it valuable.\n\n8. **Participating in Online Communities**: Engaging in forums, social media groups, and Q&A sites (like Quora) to share your expertise and link back to your content when relevant.\n\n9. **Local SEO and Citations**: For businesses, ensuring that your site is listed in local directories and that you have consistent citations can help build local backlinks.\n\n10. **Networking**: Building relationships with other bloggers and website owners in your niche to create opportunities for collaboration and link exchanges.\n\nIn summary, the most effective link building strategies in 2016 prioritized creating high-quality content and fostering genuine relationships within your industry. These approaches helped secure valuable backlinks while also enhancing your site's overall authority and visibility.",
